{
  "texts": [
    "It will be convenient to refer to them with shorthands:S 543←21, S † 543←21, Exp 3 ≡ in ⟨54|b 3 |21⟩ in, out ⟨54|a 3 |21⟩ out.",
    "(2.13)The last two are new objects: inclusive amplitudes or expectation values.",
    "We have labeled the S-matrix consistently with the operator ordering.",
    "Using (2.3) to eliminate b's we can relate them to conventional amplitudes.",
    "For example,Exp 3 = ⟨0|a 5 a 4 S † a 3 Sa † 2 a † 1 |0⟩ = X ⟨54|S † |X⟩⟨X3|S|21⟩, (2.14)which is shown on the third panel of figure 2."
  ]
}